To ask this House to adjourn in order that the'Leader of the Government may, in this matter, be placed in a higher position than he now occupies, when no advantage is to accrue to the country . by the act. is simply wrong. In looking at this question, we have to consider the cause which has forced us into our present position. Was it brought about by the Railway or otherwise? Hence Confederation appeals now, not to our party feelings, but to our patriotism.
